# AWS EC2 Website Mini Project

This project demonstrates how to host a simple website on AWS using EC2 and NGINX.

## Services Used
- Amazon EC2
- Security Groups
- Amazon Linux
- NGINX

## Steps
1. Launched an EC2 instance in a public subnet
2. Configured security group (SSH & HTTP)
3. Installed and configured NGINX
4. Deployed a simple HTML website

## Outcome
The website is accessible via the EC2 public IP.

## Security
- SSH restricted to my IP
- HTTP allowed for public access

## Cleanup
Resources were terminated after testing to avoid charges.
